ASLR (Address Space Layout Randomization) is a memory exploitation mitigation technique used on both Linux and Windows systems.

-→ How To Tyun of ASLR
→ You can just use sudo sysctl kernel. randomize_va_space=0 to temparaly disable ASLR.

-→ How does Aslr affect the stack?
→ Address Space Layout Randomisation (ASLR) is a technology used to help prevent shellcode from being successful. It does  this by randomly offsetting the location of modules and certain  in-memory structures. Data Execution Prevention (DEP) prevents certain  memory sectors